properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover, Pan American Airways, first westbound commercial flight of China Clipper, November 16-23, 1935; a. cover: green cachet on reverse with illustration of aircraft in flight over ocean and ship with text, "First flight, trans-Pacific F.A.M. route 14, San Francisco (Alameda Airport) - Honolulu"; four duplicate postmarks on front: November 16, 1935, Austin, Texas with football-shaped cancellations; one backstamp: November 23, 1935, Honolulu, Hawaii; two green 20-cent postage stamps at upper right corner and one blue 10-cent postage stamp at upper left corner; addressed to Lt. Peter Otey Ward.b. information sheet: 8 1/2 x 11 with black text; additional information prepared by donor, including route and postage information; flight cover was received mounted to sheet with photo corners with item .150 mounted on same sheet.
properties.wof:name: airmail flight cover: Pan American Airways, first westbound commercial flight of China Clipper, November 16-23, 1935
